description:
Madeleine Giovanni is seen delivering children to some Nuns at an orphanage, and we learn that she does this often. Madeleine believes that it is better to be loved than feared, it is a Machiavellian concept she expresses throughout the story.

Pietro Giovanni of the Giovanni Clan has heard tell of a painting that may contain powerful secrets painted by a Kindred(Vampire)named Draco that his vampire associates are killing each other to retrieve.

Pietro invites his cousin Isabel and his granddaughter Madeleine Giovanni to office and sends them to New York City to where it is being auctioned off to retrieve it.

They travel to New York(in coffins) and follow the arrangements made to go to the auction. There they meet with all types of old friends and foes.

We find Alvin who goes by the name of "Swayd" has turned one of her orphans from years past into a vampire or ghoul and killed his brother.

Madeleine kills Swayd and even a Don Anthony before they return with the painting.

Madeleine finds that Pietro staged the entire incident to test loyalties of his men and his family and to make them all fear him.

She is called to the orphanage to check on the children and is shown further that she suffered her own issues as a child and doesn't want children to have to feel abandoned and she actually cares for them even though she's a vampire.
name: The Machiavelli Conundrum

description:
Based on the White Wolf RPG! A TV host gets more than what she bargained for when she meets with a mysterious stranger. 48pgs, square bound, COLOR

Jane Fordham, an actress who plays Fannie Fang, the female host of Midnight Theater a horror movie showcase meets a stranger named Victor at a local watering hole. Victor tells Jane all about Cain, the first vampire and about much of vampire history. This all leads to victor taking Jane back to his place where Victor attacks Jane.

SPOILER WARNING: Click here to reveal hidden content.
Victor doesn't learn until too late that Jane is really a vampire acting like a mortal playing a vampire for TV
name: All the World's a Stage

description:
Leap into the adventures of the dynamic Defenders, comics' greatest non-team!

Bonded in a mutual mission are the mightiest misfits in the Marvel U.: the Incredible Hulk, the Sub-Mariner and the Silver Surfer. But these warriors three don't rest on bylaws and butlers; they - along with the Master of the Mystic Arts, Dr. Strange, and the defiant Valkyrie - come together only in moments of utmost crisis. Facing enemies from across the incomprehensible divide, the Defenders square off against Dormammu; the Nameless One; the Enchantress; and a dark menace from Dr. Strange's past, the sorcerer Cyrus Black. It's not just baddies they do battle with, though. In a prelude to the epic Avengers/Defenders War, Hulk, Namor and the Silver Surfer go head-to-head with the mighty Avengers in a fight that pits hero against hero like none other!

Collecting Sub-Mariner #34-35, Marvel Feature #1-3 and The Defenders #1-6.
name: Volume 1
